  title: "Comprehensive Document";
  author: "Jane Smith";
  date: "2026-01-22";
  version: "2.1";
  language: "en";
  keywords: ["example", "documentation", "osf"];
  description: "A comprehensive example showing all @meta properties";
  category: "examples";
  theme: "default";
}
*/

@doc {
  # About @meta

  The `@meta` block defines document-level metadata. It should be the
  first block in any OSF document.

  ## Required Properties

  - `title` - The document title (required)

  ## Optional Properties

  - `author` - Author name
  - `date` - Publication date (YYYY-MM-DD format)
  - `version` - Document version string
  - `language` - ISO 639-1 language code (e.g., "en", "es", "fr")
  - `keywords` - Array of keyword strings for searchability
  - `description` - Brief description of the document
  - `category` - Document category for organization
  - `theme` - Default theme for exports

  ## Usage Notes

  - Always include at least a title
  - Date should use ISO format: YYYY-MM-DD
  - Keywords help with document discovery and SEO
}
